[SHORT DESC]
Charges up the first turn; attacks on the second turn.

[LONG DESC]
<h2>Description</h2>
<p>Charges up the first turn, and then attacks on the second turn.</p>

<h2>Competitive Use</h2>
<p>Razor Wind should not be used competitively because it is a two-turn charge up Normal-type move. Body Slam or Double-Edge should always be chosen over Razor Wind in a competitive battle.</p>

<h2>Related Moves</h2>
<p><a href="/rb/moves/double-edge">Double-Edge</a> is a stronger alternative with 120 Base Power, but has recoil damage.</p>
<p><a href="/rb/moves/body_slam">Body Slam</a> is an alternative with 85 Base Power and has a 30% chance to cause paralysis.</p>